President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Duke Buchan III as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Spain, as well as to serve as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Andorra. Mr. Buchan is the Founder and CEO of Hunter Global Investors L.P. He is actively involved in educational and philanthropic causes and has established the largest single endowment at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill focused on Spanish languages, literature, and culture. He holds a B.A. in economics and Spanish from UNC, an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School, and has studied at universities in Spain. Mr. Buchan speaks Spanish and has a working knowledge of Catalan.

The President also intends to nominate Thomas J. Hushek as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of South Sudan. Mr. Hushek is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been an American diplomat since 1988. He currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of Conflict and Stabilization Operations at the Department of State. Mr. Hushek has extensive experience in management, communications, coordination of humanitarian programs, and crisis management. He has served at eight U.S. Missions overseas and holds a M.I.A. from Colombia University and a B.A. from the University of Wisconsin, Madison. He speaks Russian and Persian (Dari).